---
description: Embedded Pancreator workflow control rules
alwaysApply: true
---

The terms MUST, MUST NOT, SHOULD, SHOULD NOT, and MAY use RFC 2119 meanings.

When operating a Pancreator workflow, you MUST read the target repository's `AGENTS.md` when present, then `.pancreator/AGENTS.md` and `.pancreator/runtime/target-repo-primer.md`. You MUST NOT follow primer references unless a concrete task-specific need requires the referenced file. You MUST use `./.pancreator/bin/pan` and MUST NOT hand-edit `.pancreator/runtime/` state. CLI-emitted `runtime/`, `library/`, and `governance/` paths are harness-relative: prefix them with `.pancreator/` for Cursor filesystem access, but pass them back to the CLI without that prefix. Read the active invocation card before expanding context. Operator approvals and irreversible actions remain operator-owned.

Systematic workflow edits MUST use `./.pancreator/bin/pan changes begin|commit|cancel`. An operator-selected `/pan-spotfix` MAY edit tracked files directly only under `.pancreator/library/skills/spotfix.md` and only when no mutating workflow agent is executing against the same workspace.

`./.pancreator/bin/pan set-stage`, `pause`, and `waive-gate` are operator-only. Agents MUST NOT invoke or delegate them.
